  "texts": [
    "One can show that there is a one-parameter family of combinations which provide the correct ghost charge.",
    "These are given byk(-iσ) + (n + g -1 + k)(-2ρ -iσ -iH) + (g -1 -k)(-ρ -iσ -iH 1)+ (g -1 -k)(-ρ -iσ -iH 2) + (g -1)(ρ + iH) + n(2ρ + iσ + iH)= -(g -1)(3ρ + 3iσ + iH), for 0 ≤ k ≤ g -1, where G -only provides contributions from e -iσ and G+ only from e ρ+iH.",
    "Gcan either contribute via e -2ρ-iσ-iH Q or via the compact pieces e -ρ-iσ-iH 1 ∂ X2 and e -ρ-iσ-iH 2 ∂ X1.",
    "JHEP04(2024)048Suppose we do insert one of these compact pieces into the correlation function, for instance (e -ρ-iσ-iH 1 ∂ X2)(µ I).",
    "The contour integral around this insertion can then be deformed away from µ I."
